elements.title: Williamsburgh Savings Bank Building (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that though one publication said in 2001 that going to the Williamsburgh Savings Bank Building was like "an act of religious devotion", it was poorly suited for modern uses?

elements.title: Henry Alcazar (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that legislator Henry Alcazar successfully defended everyone accused of inciting the 1903 Water Riots that burned down the Trinidad and Tobago seat of government?

elements.title: USS Varuna (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that eight sailors on USS Varuna received the Medal of Honor for actions during the Battle of Forts Jackson and St. Philip?

elements.title: Giulia Cassini Rizzotto (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the final silent film directed by Giulia Cassini Rizzotto was partly funded by the Vatican and featured Italian aristocrats?

elements.title: taco pizza (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that a 2020 study concluded that taco pizza is the favorite pizza of Iowa?

elements.title: Khalid ibn Barmak (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Khalid ibn Barmak was so close to the first Abbasid caliph, al-Saffah, that his daughter was suckled by al-Saffah's wife?

elements.title: statue of Alexander Wood (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the now-destroyed statue of Alexander Wood was the first LGBT monument in Canada?

elements.title: Mimi Reinhardt (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Mimi Reinhardt typed Schindler's list?
